132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1094
H.P. 716 House of Representatives, March 18, 2025
An Act to Prohibit a Person from Obtaining an Elver Dealer's
License for a Minimum of 5 Years in Cases of Repeat Violations of
License Conditions
Received by the Clerk of the House on March 14, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Marine Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative SIMMONS of Waldoboro.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §6864, sub-§1-A, as amended by PL 2013, c. 492, §15, is further
3 amended to read:
4 1-A. Limits on issuance after February 1st. The department may not issue an elver
5 dealer's license or a supplemental license after February 1st of the current licensing year.
6 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §6864, sub-§1-B is enacted to read:
7 1-B. Limits on issuance to same person. The department may not issue an elver
8 dealer's license or a supplemental license to a person using the same business address as a
9 person who has violated section 6404-K, subsection 1 for at least 5 years following the
10 violation.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This bill amends the laws governing the licensing of elver dealers to provide that an
1133 elver dealer's license may not be issued to any person using the same business address as a
1144 person who has violated the conditions of the person's license for 5 years following the
1155 violation.
